result.execSummary:
The defendant David M. Deblare was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Burglary-Building or Dwelling [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class F felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.10(1m)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

superMiscConds.notes: Court orders the fines, costs, and restitution in this file shall be paid from all funds received into the defendant's prison accounts in accordance with prison policy, not to exceed 25% of gross during the term of initial confinement. If any fines, costs, and/or restitution remain outstanding at the end of the initial confinement portion of this sentence, then the remaining shall be paid as a condition of extended supervision. In the event that the Defendant is revoked or discharged from probation with outstanding financial obligations, the supervising agent shall notify the Court 10 days prior to the revocation or discharge.  A civil judgment shall be entered against the Defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement action will be used to collect the debt.

Court orders the fines, costs, and restitution in this file shall be paid from all funds received into the defendant's prison accounts in accordance with prison policy, not to exceed 25% of gross during the term of initial confinement. If any fines, costs, and/or restitution remain outstanding at the end of the initial confinement portion of this sentence, then the remaining shall be paid as a condition of extended supervision.
Defendant to undergo an alcohol and other drug assessment and comply with any further counseling and/or treatment as deemed appropriate by the supervising agent.

The defendant is to have NO CONTACT with Jorgie's Bar in Borth, The Bluff Bar & Grill in Poy Sippi, C. Jorgensen and/or S. Sattler, as named in the complaint. The defendant is to have NO CONTACT with David Cole.   The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician.

records.addlTxt: 11:20 pm case called. Defendant David M. Deblare in court with attorney Ryan Scott Ulrich.  Scott C. Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Agreement reached and stated on the record by DA Blader.   Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea QN reviewed w/Defendant.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed.  Plea:  No Contest to Count 2. Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Court dismisses and reads-in Counts 1 & 3. No statement by the defendant. Court sentences the defedant to: 8 years Wisconsin State Prison to be served as 4 years Initial Confinement and 4 years Extended Supervision. Concurrent to any other sentence the defendant is currently serving. CONDITIONS OF ES: Restitution in the amount of $2,168.81, joint and several with David Cole. No Contact with Jorgie's Bar in Borth, the Bluff Bar and Grill in Poy Sippi, C. Jorgensen and/or S. Sattler, as named in the complaint. No Contact with David Cole.   The defendant must maintain absolute sobriety, may not be present upon the premises of any bars, and is prohibited from possessing any impairing substances that have not been prescribed by a physician. AODA and follow through. Costs to be paid within 60 days or payment plan. Court authorizes 25% of inmate earnings for restitution and costs. Court finds eligible for CIP & SAP. Appeal Rights Given.
